This paper focuses on developing robust dialog policies for virtual personal assistants, which involves natural language understanding and deep reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and machine learning (cs.LG) as it uses deep reinforcement learning to learn dialog policies. Finally, the paper also involves sound processing (cs.SD) as it deals with noisy audio in realistic scenarios.
